.TH "ipr_pci_frozen" 9 "ipr_pci_frozen" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ipr_pci_frozen \- Called when slot has experienced a PCI bus error.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" ipr_pci_frozen
.BI "(struct pci_dev *pdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pdev" 12
PCI device struct
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This routine is called to tell us that the PCI bus
is down. Can't do anything here, except put the device driver
into a holding pattern, waiting for the PCI bus to come back.
